top_mem:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr⊤» -/
/-- A specific witness of `pfilter.nonempty` when `P` has a top element. -/
@[simp]
theorem top_mem : «expr⊤» ∈ F :=
  ideal.bot_mem _
#align top_mem top_mem
principal_le_principal_iff:
theorem principal_le_principal_iff {p q : P} : principal q ≤ principal p ↔ p ≤ q := by simp
#align principal_le_principal_iff principal_le_principal_iff
principal_le_iff:
@[simp]
theorem principal_le_iff {F : pfilter P} : principal x ≤ F ↔ x ∈ F :=
  ideal.principal_le_iff
#align principal_le_iff principal_le_iff
of_def:
/-

Authors: Mathieu Guay-Paquet

theorem is_pfilter.of_def [preorder P] {F : set P} (nonempty : F.nonempty) (directed : DirectedOn (· ≥ ·) F)
    (mem_of_le : ∀ {x y : P}, x ≤ y → x ∈ F → y ∈ F) : is_pfilter F :=
  ⟨fun _ _ _ _ => mem_of_le ‹_› ‹_›, nonempty, Directed⟩
#align is_pfilter.of_def is_pfilter.of_def
nonempty:
theorem nonempty : (F : set P).nonempty :=
  F.dual.nonempty
#align nonempty nonempty
mem_principal:
@[simp]
theorem mem_principal : x ∈ principal y ↔ y ≤ x :=
  ideal.mem_principal
#align mem_principal mem_principal
mem_of_mem_of_le:
@[trans]
theorem mem_of_mem_of_le {F G : pfilter P} : x ∈ F → F ≤ G → x ∈ G :=
  ideal.mem_of_mem_of_le
#align mem_of_mem_of_le mem_of_mem_of_le
mem_of_le:
theorem mem_of_le {F : pfilter P} : x ≤ y → x ∈ F → y ∈ F := fun h => F.dual.lower h
#align mem_of_le mem_of_le
mem_def:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ᵒᵈ» -/
@[simp]
theorem mem_def (x : P) (I : ideal («expr ᵒᵈ» P)) : x ∈ (⟨I⟩ : pfilter P) ↔ OrderDual.toDual x ∈ I :=
  iff.rfl
#align mem_def mem_def
mem_coe:
@[simp]
theorem mem_coe : x ∈ (F : set P) ↔ x ∈ F :=
  iff_of_eq rfl
#align mem_coe mem_coe
is_pfilter:
theorem is_pfilter : is_pfilter (F : set P) :=
  F.dual.is_ideal
#align is_pfilter is_pfilter
inf_mem_iff:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⊓ » -/
@[simp]
theorem inf_mem_iff : «expr ⊓ » x y ∈ F ↔ x ∈ F ∧ y ∈ F :=
  ideal.sup_mem_iff
#align inf_mem_iff inf_mem_iff
inf_mem:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⊓ » -/
/-- A specific witness of `pfilter.directed` when `P` has meets. -/
theorem inf_mem (hx : x ∈ F) (hy : y ∈ F) : «expr ⊓ » x y ∈ F :=
  ideal.sup_mem hx hy
#align inf_mem inf_mem
ext:
/-- Two filters are equal when their underlying sets are equal. -/
@[ext]
theorem ext (h : (s : set P) = t) : s = t := by
  cases s
  cases t
  exact congr_arg _ (ideal.ext h)
#align ext ext
antitone_principal:
-- defeq abuse
theorem antitone_principal : antitone (principal : P → pfilter P) := by delta antitone <;> simp
#align antitone_principal antitone_principal
Inf_gc:
theorem Inf_gc :
    GaloisConnection (fun x => OrderDual.toDual (principal x)) fun F => infₛ (OrderDual.ofDual F : pfilter P) :=
  fun x F => by
  simp
  rfl
#align Inf_gc Inf_gc
Directed:
#print Directed /-
theorem Directed : DirectedOn (· ≥ ·) (F : set P) :=
  F.dual.directed
#align directed Directed
